The [Webconverger 6.2](http://download.webconverger.org/webc-6.2.txt) security release applies the [APSB10-14 security update
for the Adobe Flash
Player](http://www.adobe.com/support/security/bulletins/apsb10-14.html). Patching [numerous remote code execution bugs second to only
Oracle](http://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=1&eotf=1&u=http://blog.fefe.de/%3Fts%3Db2ef379a&sl=de&tl=en)!

Surprisingly this is the first update for almost 4 months. In its current
(Debian Live **lenny**) design Webconverger has reached maturity as a piece of
software. Another reason to deploy Webconverger for conservative institutions.

Download it from the [German mirror](http://download.webconverger.org/) or the [Webconverger download mirror in California](http://download.webconverger.com/).

